{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_014FJnApFULnybyEREebaB7E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are satisfied:\n\n**Root cause:** Two separate issues were masking each other:\n1. **Permission misconfiguration** — `app-user` had no permissions on `/app` (or anywhere), while `ops-user` had incorrectly been granted full `.*`/`.*`/`.*` access to `/app` (a vhost it shouldn't touch) and had no permissions on its own `/ops`.\n2. **Masked queue-argument mismatch** — once permissions were fixed, `app-client` failed a separate way: it tried to (re)declare the existing `app-queue` in `/app` without the `x-queue-mode: lazy` argument that `app-producer` had already declared it with, causing a RabbitMQ `inequivalent arg` rejection.\n\n**Fixes applied (native K8s/CLI only):**\n- `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user '.*' '.*' '.*'`\n- `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user '.*' '.*' '.*'`\n- `rabbitmqctl clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` (removed the out-of-scope grant)\n- Patched the `app-client` Deployment's container command (`kubectl patch --type=json`) to add `x-queue-mode: lazy` to its queue-declare payload, matching `app-producer`.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `/app` permissions: `admin`, `app-user` only (full `.*`/`.*`/`.*`) — no `ops-user`.\n- `/ops` permissions: `admin`, `ops-user` only (full `.*`/`.*`/`.*`) — no `app-user`.\n- `app-client`, `app-producer`, `ops-client` deployments all `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts.\n- RabbitMQ cluster shows all 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) as running."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1153,"cache_read_input_tokens":57034,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1153},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_